{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7f318ee3-5c2a-4325-aeeb-88b9fcd8725a","content":"Here's what to update:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{\n  \"sdk\": {\n    \"version\": \"11.0.100\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**4. Additional steps:**\n- Install the .NET 11 SDK locally\n- Run `dotnet restore` to update dependencies\n- Check for deprecated APIs or breaking changes in the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/compatibility/)\n- Update any NuGet packages (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`) to their 11.x versions","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3e7a12c0-40d9-41ff-8a9b-d2081e6dcf01","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to update their .NET 10 ASP.NET Core web app to .NET 11. This is a straightforward knowledge question — I can answer directly without needing tools.","outputTokens":287,"requestId":"9842:7AD2E:236C3F:2C5664:69F55664"},"id":"cd97beb2-b4d6-44f3-a0ce-ca66c4b1447c","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:42:02.531Z","parentId":"51e6f4de-6de8-46cf-b2cf-749d7e1eebf2"}
